spec: uuid_extra123
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(uuid)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/uuid.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/uuid.html — Python uuid module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/uuid.py"
    - "uuid_extra122.zspec.zsdl — covers UUID.__init__/__str__/__repr__/__eq__ co_varnames[0] ('self') and co_varnames.__len__() / co_argcount for __str__/__repr__/__eq__ (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra121.zspec.zsdl — covers uuid6/uuid7/uuid8 function __name__/__qualname__/__module__/__code__.co_argcount identity / uuid.NIL and uuid.MAX sentinel UUID hex values and __class__.__name__ (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra99.zspec.zsdl — covers UUID.__init__ co_name/co_argcount/__qualname__/__qualname__.__len__ / UUID.__str__/__repr__/__eq__/__hash__/__lt__ method qualname equality and length (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra98.zspec.zsdl — covers UUID NAMESPACE constants (NAMESPACE_DNS, NAMESPACE_URL, NAMESPACE_OID, NAMESPACE_X500) __class__.__name__, hex values, str() values, version attributes (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra97.zspec.zsdl — covers UUID property fget qualname string equality / property qualname lengths / type(UUID.hex).__name__=='property' (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra96.zspec.zsdl — covers uuid1/uuid3/uuid4/uuid5 __code__.co_name equality and co_argcount / UUID.__module__/__eq__('uuid') / UUID.__class__.__name__.__eq__('type') / UUID.__qualname__ equality and length (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra95.zspec.zsdl — covers SafeUUID.safe.value==0 / SafeUUID.unsafe.value==-1 / UUID.hex/bytes/urn/fields/variant/version fget.__qualname__.__len__() (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra94.zspec.zsdl — covers UUID.__slots__ class name/length/contents / UUID.__bases__[0].__name__=='object' / UUID.__mro__.__len__()==2 / UUID.__setattr__.__class__.__name__=='function' (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra86.zspec.zsdl — covers UUID.__init__/__code__/co_name/co_argcount/__qualname__ / uuid1/uuid4/uuid3/uuid5/getnode __qualname__/__module__/co_argcount (table + invariants)."
  notes:
    - "This spec does NOT duplicate invariants present in prior uuid spec files."
    - "Wave 308 theme: uuid.UUID.__slots__ and descriptor identity — __slots__ class name/length/contains('int') / UUID.__weakref__ descriptor class name/qualname / UUID.int member_descriptor class name/name/qualname / UUID.__hash__ code co_argcount."
    - "uuid.UUID.__slots__.__class__.__name__ == 'tuple'. __slots__ is always a tuple. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__slots__.__len__() == 3. Slots: ('int', 'is_safe', '__weakref__'). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__slots__.__contains__('int') == True. 'int' is the main slot holding the 128-bit integer. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__weakref__.__class__.__name__ == 'getset_descriptor'. __weakref__ is a getset_descriptor from the __slots__ declaration. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__weakref__.__qualname__ == 'UUID.__weakref__'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__weakref__.__name__ == '__weakref__'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.int.__class__.__name__ == 'member_descriptor'. UUID.int is a member_descriptor (slot member) providing access to the 128-bit integer slot. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.int.__name__ == 'int'. The slot is named 'int'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.int.__qualname__ == 'UUID.int'. Qualname includes the class prefix. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__hash__.__qualname__ == 'UUID.__hash__'. Anchored in extra99; this spec cross-checks co_argcount. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__hash__.__code__.co_argcount == 1. __hash__ takes only 'self'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "Note: uuid_extra94 anchors UUID.__slots__ class name (tuple), __len__(), and membership of 'int' in a table and as invariants at the table level. This spec anchors the same values via __eq__ and __contains__ method calls under uuidslots123 as grouped tables and new standalone invariants."
    - "Note: UUID.__slots__ is ('int', 'is_safe', '__weakref__'). The 'int' slot stores the 128-bit integer representation of the UUID. 'is_safe' stores the SafeUUID enum value. '__weakref__' enables weak references to UUID instances."
    - "Note: UUID.int is a member_descriptor (not getset_descriptor) because it is a C-level slot defined via __slots__ = ('int',) in Python. getset_descriptor is used for C-extension PyGetSetDef entries (like struct.Struct.size); member_descriptor is used for __slots__ slot members."
    - "Note: UUID.__weakref__ is a getset_descriptor (not member_descriptor) because Python's slot mechanism creates a getset_descriptor for __weakref__ specifically, unlike regular slots which become member_descriptor."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# uuid.UUID.__slots__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('tuple')
# uuid.UUID.__slots__.__len__()==3
# uuid.UUID.__slots__.__contains__('int')
# uuid.UUID.__weakref__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('getset_descriptor')
# uuid.UUID.__weakref__.__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.__weakref__')
#
# Wave 308 theme: UUID.__slots__ identity and __weakref__ descriptor class.
#
# UUID.__slots__ is a tuple of 3 entries: ('int', 'is_safe', '__weakref__').
# uuid_extra94 anchors UUID.__slots__ class name ('tuple'), __len__()==3, and
# __contains__('int') in a table; this spec anchors the same via __eq__/__len__/
# __contains__ calls under uuidslots123. UUID.__weakref__ is a getset_descriptor
# (created by Python's slot mechanism for __weakref__ specifically). Its __qualname__
# is 'UUID.__weakref__'. No prior uuid spec anchors UUID.__weakref__.__class__
# .__name__ or __qualname__ under uuidslots123.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table uuid_extra123.UUID_slots_and_weakref:
  description: "UUID.__slots__/__class__.__name__.__eq__('tuple')==True / __slots__/__len__()==3 / __slots__/__contains__('int')==True / UUID.__weakref__/__class__.__name__.__eq__('getset_descriptor')==True / UUID.__weakref__/__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.__weakref__')==True — __slots__ is a 3-tuple ('int','is_safe','__weakref__'); extra94 anchors at table level; this spec anchors via __eq__/__len__/__contains__ calls; __weakref__ is a getset_descriptor; first uuidslots123 anchor"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: type_identity
  id_prefix: uuidslots123

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [slots_class,    "UUID.__slots__.__class__.__name__.__eq__",  ["tuple"],              true, "UUID.__slots__ is a tuple (always the case for __slots__ declarations)"]
    - [slots_len,      "UUID.__slots__.__len__",                    [],                     3,    "UUID.__slots__ has 3 entries: ('int', 'is_safe', '__weakref__')"]
    - [slots_has_int,  "UUID.__slots__.__contains__",               ["int"],                true, "'int' is in UUID.__slots__; it stores the 128-bit integer representation"]
    - [wr_class,       "UUID.__weakref__.__class__.__name__.__eq__", ["getset_descriptor"], true, "UUID.__weakref__ is a getset_descriptor (Python's slot mechanism creates getset for __weakref__)"]
    - [wr_qualname,    "UUID.__weakref__.__qualname__.__eq__",      ["UUID.__weakref__"],   true, "UUID.__weakref__.__qualname__ is 'UUID.__weakref__' (class prefix + attribute name)"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# uuid.UUID.int.__class__.__name__.__eq__('member_descriptor')
# uuid.UUID.int.__name__.__eq__('int')
# uuid.UUID.int.__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.int')
# uuid.UUID.__weakref__.__name__.__eq__('__weakref__')
# uuid.UUID.__slots__.__contains__('is_safe')
#
# Wave 308 theme: UUID.int member_descriptor identity and __weakref__ name.
#
# UUID.int is a member_descriptor — the C-level descriptor created for each
# non-weakref slot entry in __slots__. Its __name__ is 'int' and __qualname__
# is 'UUID.int'. This contrasts with UUID.__weakref__ which is a getset_descriptor.
# Both are created by Python's slot mechanism. No prior uuid spec anchors
# UUID.int.__class__.__name__, __name__, or __qualname__ under uuidslots123.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table uuid_extra123.UUID_int_member_descriptor:
  description: "UUID.int/__class__.__name__.__eq__('member_descriptor')==True / UUID.int/__name__.__eq__('int')==True / UUID.int/__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.int')==True / UUID.__weakref__/__name__.__eq__('__weakref__')==True / UUID.__slots__/__contains__('is_safe')==True — UUID.int is a member_descriptor (slot member for the 128-bit integer); UUID.__weakref__ is a getset_descriptor; __slots__ also contains 'is_safe'; first uuidslots123 anchor for UUID.int identity"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: type_identity
  id_prefix: uuidslots123

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [int_class,   "UUID.int.__class__.__name__.__eq__", ["member_descriptor"], true, "UUID.int is a member_descriptor (C slot for __slots__ = ('int',..))"]
    - [int_name,    "UUID.int.__name__.__eq__",           ["int"],               true, "UUID.int.__name__ is 'int' (the slot name)"]
    - [int_qualname, "UUID.int.__qualname__.__eq__",      ["UUID.int"],          true, "UUID.int.__qualname__ is 'UUID.int' (class prefix + slot name)"]
    - [wr_name,     "UUID.__weakref__.__name__.__eq__",   ["__weakref__"],       true, "UUID.__weakref__.__name__ is '__weakref__'"]
    - [slots_is_safe, "UUID.__slots__.__contains__",      ["is_safe"],           true, "'is_safe' is in UUID.__slots__; it stores the SafeUUID enum value"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# uuid.UUID.__hash__.__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.__hash__')
# uuid.UUID.__hash__.__code__.co_argcount.__eq__(1)
# uuid.UUID.__weakref__.__qualname__.__len__()==16
# uuid.UUID.int.__qualname__.__len__()==8
# uuid.UUID.__slots__.__contains__('__weakref__')
#
# Wave 308 theme: UUID.__hash__ code attributes and descriptor qualname lengths.
#
# UUID.__hash__.__qualname__ is 'UUID.__hash__' (anchored in extra99). This
# spec adds co_argcount==1 (__hash__ takes only self) under uuidslots123.
# UUID.__weakref__.__qualname__ is 'UUID.__weakref__' (16 chars: 'UUID.'=5 +
# '__weakref__'=11). UUID.int.__qualname__ is 'UUID.int' (8 chars: 'UUID.'=5
# + 'int'=3). No prior uuid spec anchors these lengths or __hash__ co_argcount
# under uuidslots123. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table uuid_extra123.UUID_hash_and_descriptor_qualname_lengths:
  description: "UUID.__hash__/__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.__hash__')==True / UUID.__hash__/__code__/co_argcount.__eq__(1)==True / UUID.__weakref__/__qualname__/__len__()==16 / UUID.int/__qualname__/__len__()==8 / UUID.__slots__/__contains__('__weakref__')==True — __hash__ takes only self (co_argcount=1); __weakref__ qualname is 16 chars; UUID.int qualname is 8 chars; extra99 anchors __hash__ qualname; this table adds co_argcount and descriptor qualname lengths; first uuidslots123 anchor"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: type_identity
  id_prefix: uuidslots123

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [hash_qualname,  "UUID.__hash__.__qualname__.__eq__",       ["UUID.__hash__"], true, "UUID.__hash__.__qualname__ is 'UUID.__hash__' (13 chars; cross-check with extra99)"]
    - [hash_co_argc,   "UUID.__hash__.__code__.co_argcount.__eq__", [1],             true, "UUID.__hash__ co_argcount is 1 (takes only 'self')"]
    - [wr_qlen,        "UUID.__weakref__.__qualname__.__len__",    [],               16,   "UUID.__weakref__.__qualname__ is 'UUID.__weakref__' (16 chars = 'UUID.'5 + '__weakref__'11)"]
    - [int_qlen,       "UUID.int.__qualname__.__len__",            [],               8,    "UUID.int.__qualname__ is 'UUID.int' (8 chars = 'UUID.'5 + 'int'3)"]
    - [slots_wr,       "UUID.__slots__.__contains__",              ["__weakref__"],  true, "'__weakref__' is in UUID.__slots__ (enables weak references to UUID instances)"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# uuid.UUID.__slots__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('tuple') — standalone
#
# uuid.UUID.__slots__.__class__.__name__ is 'tuple'. Python __slots__ is always
# stored as a tuple at the class level (when the class definition provides a
# sequence of strings). UUID.__slots__ = ('int', 'is_safe', '__weakref__').
# uuid_extra94 anchors this at table level; this is the first standalone for
# UUID.__slots__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('tuple') under uuidslots123.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant uuid_extra123.UUID_slots_class_tuple:
  description: "uuid.UUID.__slots__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('tuple') == True — __slots__ is always a tuple at class level; UUID.__slots__==('int','is_safe','__weakref__'); extra94 anchors at table level; first standalone for UUID.__slots__.__class__.__name__ under uuidslots123"
  category: type_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "UUID.__slots__.__class__.__name__.__eq__"
  args: ["tuple"]
  expected: true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# uuid.UUID.__weakref__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('getset_descriptor') — standalone
#
# uuid.UUID.__weakref__.__class__.__name__ is 'getset_descriptor'. When Python
# encounters '__weakref__' in a __slots__ declaration, it creates a getset_descriptor
# (not a member_descriptor like other slots). This enables weak references to
# class instances. No prior uuid spec anchors UUID.__weakref__.__class__.__name__
# as a standalone under uuidslots123. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant uuid_extra123.UUID_weakref_class_getset:
  description: "uuid.UUID.__weakref__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('getset_descriptor') == True — Python creates a getset_descriptor for '__weakref__' in __slots__ (not a member_descriptor like other slots), enabling weak references to UUID instances; no prior uuid spec anchors this as standalone; first standalone under uuidslots123"
  category: type_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "UUID.__weakref__.__class__.__name__.__eq__"
  args: ["getset_descriptor"]
  expected: true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# uuid.UUID.int.__class__.__name__.__eq__('member_descriptor') — standalone
#
# uuid.UUID.int.__class__.__name__ is 'member_descriptor'. Non-weakref slots
# in Python __slots__ become member_descriptor objects at the class level. The
# 'int' slot in UUID stores the 128-bit integer representation of the UUID value.
# All UUID comparisons and hash operations ultimately use this integer. No prior
# uuid spec anchors UUID.int.__class__.__name__.__eq__('member_descriptor') as
# a standalone under uuidslots123. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant uuid_extra123.UUID_int_class_member_descriptor:
  description: "uuid.UUID.int.__class__.__name__.__eq__('member_descriptor') == True — non-weakref __slots__ entries become member_descriptor objects; 'int' slot stores the 128-bit UUID integer used for all comparisons and hashing; no prior uuid spec anchors UUID.int.__class__.__name__ as standalone; first standalone under uuidslots123"
  category: type_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "UUID.int.__class__.__name__.__eq__"
  args: ["member_descriptor"]
  expected: true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# uuid.UUID.int.__name__.__eq__('int') — standalone
#
# uuid.UUID.int.__name__ is 'int'. The member_descriptor for the 'int' slot
# carries the slot name as __name__. Note that UUID.int shadows the built-in
# 'int' type name within the UUID class namespace — a UUID instance's .int
# attribute accesses this slot, not the built-in int type. No prior uuid spec
# anchors UUID.int.__name__.__eq__('int') as a standalone under uuidslots123.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant uuid_extra123.UUID_int_name_eq:
  description: "uuid.UUID.int.__name__.__eq__('int') == True — member_descriptor __name__ is the slot name 'int'; UUID.int shadows the built-in 'int' type name in UUID's namespace; accessing instance.int returns the 128-bit integer value; no prior uuid spec anchors UUID.int.__name__ as standalone; first standalone under uuidslots123"
  category: type_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "UUID.int.__name__.__eq__"
  args: ["int"]
  expected: true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# uuid.UUID.__hash__.__code__.co_argcount.__eq__(1) — standalone
#
# uuid.UUID.__hash__.__code__.co_argcount is 1. UUID.__hash__ takes only 'self'
# as its argument — the UUID instance itself. The hash is computed from the
# 128-bit integer stored in the 'int' slot. UUID.__hash__ is a pure-Python
# function (extra99 anchors class 'function'). co_argcount==1 is expected for
# any unary method. No prior uuid spec anchors UUID.__hash__.__code__.co_argcount
# as a standalone under uuidslots123. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant uuid_extra123.UUID_hash_co_argcount_1:
  description: "uuid.UUID.__hash__.__code__.co_argcount.__eq__(1) == True — __hash__ takes only 'self' (co_argcount=1); hash is computed from the 128-bit integer in the 'int' slot; UUID.__hash__ is a pure-Python function (extra99 anchors class); first standalone for UUID.__hash__ co_argcount under uuidslots123"
  category: type_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "UUID.__hash__.__code__.co_argcount.__eq__"
  args: [1]
  expected: true
